### **Notable “stub / placeholder” implementations (even without TODO macros)**

- **Provider spokes are placeholders** (all providers return constant strings; registry doesn’t really route by capability):

```13:55:/home/mega/Chyren/omega_workspace/workspace/OmegA-Next/omega-spokes/src/lib.rs
pub struct AnthropicProvider { pub api_key: String }
#[async_trait]
impl Provider for AnthropicProvider {
    fn name(&self) -> String { "anthropic".into() }
    async fn generate(&self, _p: &str) -> anyhow::Result<String> { Ok("Anthropic".into()) }
}
// ... OpenAIProvider / GeminiProvider similar ...
impl SpokeRegistry {
    pub fn find_tool_provider(&self, _cap: SpokeCapability) -> Option<&Box<dyn Provider>> {
        self.providers.values().next()
    }
    pub fn spokes_with_capability(&self, _cap: SpokeCapability) -> Vec<String> {
        self.providers.keys().cloned().collect()
    }
